ce:section.ce:para:
The membrane intrinsic transport properties, pure water permeability constant (A, L m−2 h−1 bar−1) and solute permeability constant (B, L m−2 h−1), were determined using a cross-flow reverse osmosis (RO) system [32] whose membrane cell has an effective membrane area (A

                           m
                        ) of 8.07 cm2, under a pressure of 10 bar, a flow rate of 150 mL min−1, and temperature of 25 °C. DI water and 1000 mg L−1 NaCl were used as the feed for determination of A and B, respectively.
